==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fulminate of mercury
<hw>ful"mi*nate of mer"cu*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The mercury salt of fulminic acid
(<chform>Hg(CNO)2</chform>), called also <altname>mercury
fulminate</altname>. It is prepared as gray crystals, and is used
primarily in detonators for detonating high explosives, such as dynamite
or TNT.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fulminating</ent>⟦br⟧
